## Installation
First you need to install ProtocolBuffers 3.0.0-beta-3 or later.

```sh
mkdir tmp
cd tmp
git clone https://github.com/google/protobuf
cd protobuf
./autogen.sh
./configure
make
make check
sudo make install
```

Then, `go get -u` as usual the following packages:

```sh
go get -u github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/protoc-gen-grpc-gateway
go get -u github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/protoc-gen-swagger
go get -u github.com/golang/protobuf/protoc-gen-go
```
next you will need to compile the proto files so we can access the service:

```sh
export QEMU_ROOT="$my_repo/external/qemu"
mkdir $GOPATH/src/android_emulation_control
protoc -I/usr/local/include -I$QEMU_ROOT \
  -I$GOPATH/src \
  -I$GOPATH/src/github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/third_party/googleapis \
  --go_out=plugins=grpc:/tmp \
  $QEMU_ROOT/android/android-emu/android/emulation/control/emulator_controller.proto
protoc -I/usr/local/include -I$QEMU_ROOT -I$GOPATH/src \
       -I$GOPATH/src/github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/third_party/googleapis \
       --grpc-gateway_out=logtostderr=true,grpc_api_configuration=$QEMU_ROOT/android/android-emu/android/emulation/control/api_config.yaml:/tmp \
       $QEMU_ROOT/android/android-emu/android/emulation/control/emulator_controller.proto
```

Next we can place them in the right location on the $GOPATH and run the http bridge:

```sh
mv  /tmp/android/android-emu/android/emulation/control/emulator_controller*  $GO_PATH/src/android_emulation_control
cd $QEMU_ROOT/android/android-emu/android/emulation/control/grpc-samples
go httpbridge.go
```

Now you should be able to access the emulator over http as follows:

```sh
curl -H "Accept: application/json" -X POST -d '{"key": "30"}' http://localhost:8080/v1/key
```

